<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Overview">Overview</span></h2>
<p>An unusual ship given as a quest reward by the Goners.
</p><p>It is compatible with nearly all weapon systems in the X-Universe.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Background">Background</span></h2>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Physical_Characteristics">Physical Characteristics</span></h2>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Combat"> Combat </span></h2>
<p>While relatively lightly armored for a M6 class ship, the unusual variety of weapons allowed make the Truelight Seeker unusually lethal.
</p><p>The Gauss Cannon is typically only permitted on M1 and M2 class ships. High damage and long range, combined with the sustained fire capability afforded by their ammo requirement, make the Truelight Seeker a significant threat. However, permitted only 400 MJ in shielding and average M6 speed, the Truelight Seeker is at a disadvantage in a slugging match, rendering it an eggshell armed with a sledgehammer.
</p><p>Against M6 or lesser vehicles, a tactic available to the Truelight Seeker is to utilize the greater range afforded by the heavy guns and try to cripple enemies before they can get close enough to fight back, then retreating to a standoff position to finish them off.
</p><p>Against M7, M2 and M1 ships, the Truelight Seeker must rely on its greater speed and much smaller profile to avoid fire, while replying with equivalent weapons.
</p><p>Against a swarm of M5 ships the Truelight Seeker may employ the PSG, which is capable of covering a broad cone in front of the ship.
</p><p>In close quarters combat, the lack of independent turrets does hurt as it is unable to defend itself against attacks in multiple directions.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Equipment"> Equipment </span></h2>
<ul><li><a href="/index.php/Wasp_Missile" title="Wasp Missile">Wasp Missile</a>
</li><li><a href="/index.php/Silkworm_Missile" title="Silkworm Missile">Silkworm Missile</a>
</li><li><a href="/index.php/Disruptor_Missile" title="Disruptor Missile">Disruptor Missile</a>
</li><li><a href="/index.php/Hurricane_Missile" title="Hurricane Missile">Hurricane Missile</a>
</li><li><a href="/index.php/Remote_Guided_Warhead" title="Remote Guided Warhead">Remote Guided Warhead</a>
</li><li><a href="/index.php/Wildfire_Missile" title="Wildfire Missile">Wildfire Missile</a>
</li></ul>
<p>Unsuprisingly, the TLS isn't compatible with kyon or spare lasers. However, the TLS is very unusual in being unable to equip IRE weapons.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Availability"> Availability </span></h2>
<p>The Truelight Seeker may be acquired by completing a quest chain for the Goners.
</p>
<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Suggested_Roles"> Suggested Roles</span></h2>
<p>Long range high damage weapons, coupled with light shields, make this ship better in standoff roles as fire support or artillery.
</p>
